[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1771},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F15\u002Fdiscord-bot-with-openai-gpt3\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F15\u002Fdiscord-bot-with-openai-gpt3\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F15\u002Fdiscord-bot-with-openai-gpt3\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F15\u002Fdiscord-bot-with-openai-gpt3\u002F":1746,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F15\u002Fdiscord-bot-with-openai-gpt3\u002F":1755},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20221215\u002F2411869749\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1728,"date":1729,"description":1730,"extension":1731,"lang":1732,"meta":1733,"navigation":395,"path":1734,"readingMinutes":1735,"seo":1736,"standalone":1737,"stem":1738,"tags":1739,"tldr":1742,"updated":1743,"url":1744,"__hash__":1745},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fdiscord-bot-with-openai-gpt3.md","Building a Discord Chatbot with OpenAI GPT-3","2418697423",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1714},"minimark",[11,16,20,36,40,43,46,64,67,71,80,87,90,96,99,105,112,115,121,124,130,133,139,142,148,151,154,161,164,167,173,176,182,185,188,194,199,202,206,209,252,255,281,302,309,312,316,319,324,327,588,591,619,634,637,656,679,883,893,899,902,906,917,1260,1263,1285,1295,1307,1556,1563,1569,1574,1578,1581,1589,1592,1601,1604,1610,1613,1616,1619,1623,1626,1633,1637,1640,1663,1666,1670,1673,1688,1695,1702,1710],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"This post walks through building a Discord chatbot using OpenAI GPT-3 — one that can reply to your messages. Discord is actually a really good fit for integrating with OpenAI. The main focus is GPT-3, but the sample repo also includes GPT-3.5 commits for reference.",[21,22,25],"callout",{"title":23,"type":24},"Warning","warning",[17,26,27,28,35],{},"You'll need to apply for your own OpenAI Key. For the application process, see ",[29,30,34],"a",{"href":31,"rel":32},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fnodejs\u002F20221210\u002F1224824056\u002F#%E7%94%B3%E8%AB%8B-OpenAI-API",[33],"nofollow","this post (article in Mandarin)",".",[12,37,39],{"id":38},"preamble","Preamble",[17,41,42],{},"I'm not going to cover Node.js, Git, GitHub, npm basics in this post — it'd get way too long.",[17,44,45],{},"But if you're not familiar with npm and Git commands, here are some earlier posts (in Mandarin):",[47,48,49,57],"ul",{},[50,51,52],"li",{},[29,53,56],{"href":54,"rel":55},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fhexo\u002F20200921\u002F849819598\u002F",[33],"(8) Try Learning Hexo - Basic npm commands you should know (article in Mandarin)",[50,58,59],{},[29,60,63],{"href":61,"rel":62},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fgit\u002F20190615\u002F1148594701\u002F",[33],"Basic Git commands (article in Mandarin)",[17,65,66],{},"I'll include the sample code GitHub link at the end, with README notes so you can quickly run a Discord bot yourself.",[12,68,70],{"id":69},"discord-setup","Discord setup",[17,72,73,74,79],{},"First step — create a Discord bot. Go to the ",[29,75,78],{"href":76,"rel":77},"https:\u002F\u002Fdiscord.com\u002Fdevelopers\u002Fapplications",[33],"Discord Developer Portal"," and click Application.",[17,81,82],{},[83,84],"img",{"alt":85,"src":86},"Application","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fa0Od41t.png",[17,88,89],{},"Click \"New Application\".",[17,91,92],{},[83,93],{"alt":94,"src":95},"New Application","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FaEa0M5F.png",[17,97,98],{},"It'll ask for a bot name — let's go with \"OpenAI GPT-3\".",[17,100,101],{},[83,102],{"alt":103,"src":104},"OpenAI GPT-3","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FcFSnLzP.png",[21,106,109],{"title":107,"type":108},"Note","note",[17,110,111],{},"This is the application name, not the bot's display name. It'll also become the role name on your Discord server, so pick something good.",[17,113,114],{},"Inside the \"OpenAI GPT-3\" application page, we need to create a bot. Click \"Bot\" on the left.",[17,116,117],{},[83,118],{"alt":119,"src":120},"Bot","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FbaUchls.png",[17,122,123],{},"Click \"Add Bot\" on the right.",[17,125,126],{},[83,127],{"alt":128,"src":129},"Add Bot","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FvnpXA5Y.png",[17,131,132],{},"Discord asks you to confirm. Click \"Yes, do it!\".",[17,134,135],{},[83,136],{"alt":137,"src":138},"Yes, do it!","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FN6LdkrN.png",[17,140,141],{},"Your bot now appears. Find the \"Token\" field and click \"Reset Token\".",[17,143,144],{},[83,145],{"alt":146,"src":147},"Reset Token","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FA5iTEwZ.png",[17,149,150],{},"You'll get a Token string — your bot's Token. Save it, we'll need it later.",[17,152,153],{},"Don't share your bot Token with anyone — they could take control of your bot.",[17,155,156,160],{},[157,158,159],"code",{},"Username"," will be your bot's display name. In my sample code, I called mine \"妙麗·格蘭傑\" (Hermione Granger).",[17,162,163],{},"Important — scroll down to find \"Privileged Gateway Intents\" and turn on \"Message Content Intent\", otherwise the bot can't receive messages.",[17,165,166],{},"Next, add the bot to your Discord server. Click \"OAuth2\" on the left, then \"URL Generator\" (the easier method).",[17,168,169],{},[83,170],{"alt":171,"src":172},"URL Generator","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FLtQioGX.png",[17,174,175],{},"In the \"SCOPES\" section, check \"bot\". In \"BOT PERMISSIONS\", check \"Send Messages\".",[17,177,178],{},[83,179],{"alt":180,"src":181},"Send Messages","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FeiUZwyz.png",[17,183,184],{},"We only need the bot to reply to messages, so only \"Send Messages\" is needed. If you want more functionality, check additional permissions.",[17,186,187],{},"Below you'll see a \"Generated URL\" section. Copy that URL, paste into your browser, hit Enter. You'll see a screen for choosing which server to add the bot to. Pick yours and add the bot.",[17,189,190],{},[83,191],{"alt":192,"src":193},"Add to Bot","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FePRXynz.png",[17,195,196],{},[83,197],{"alt":192,"src":198},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FpbMp7A7.png",[17,200,201],{},"Bot's now in your server. Basic Discord bot setup done.",[12,203,205],{"id":204},"project-environment","Project environment",[17,207,208],{},"Create a folder — let's call it \"discord-bot\" — and initialize:",[210,211,216],"pre",{"className":212,"code":213,"language":214,"meta":215,"style":215},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","mkdir discord-bot\ncd discord-bot\nnpm init -y\n","bash","",[157,217,218,231,240],{"__ignoreMap":215},[219,220,223,227],"span",{"class":221,"line":222},"line",1,[219,224,226],{"class":225},"smYoP","mkdir",[219,228,230],{"class":229},"sWayO"," discord-bot\n",[219,232,234,238],{"class":221,"line":233},2,[219,235,237],{"class":236},"stw71","cd",[219,239,230],{"class":229},[219,241,243,246,249],{"class":221,"line":242},3,[219,244,245],{"class":225},"npm",[219,247,248],{"class":229}," init",[219,250,251],{"class":236}," -y\n",[17,253,254],{},"Install the packages we need:",[47,256,257,265,273],{},[50,258,259,260],{},"dotenv\n",[47,261,262],{},[50,263,264],{},"Reads .env files",[50,266,267,268],{},"discord.js\n",[47,269,270],{},[50,271,272],{},"For Discord operations",[50,274,275,276],{},"openai\n",[47,277,278],{},[50,279,280],{},"For OpenAI GPT-3 operations",[210,282,284],{"className":212,"code":283,"language":214,"meta":215,"style":215},"npm install dotenv discord.js openai\n",[157,285,286],{"__ignoreMap":215},[219,287,288,290,293,296,299],{"class":221,"line":222},[219,289,245],{"class":225},[219,291,292],{"class":229}," install",[219,294,295],{"class":229}," dotenv",[219,297,298],{"class":229}," discord.js",[219,300,301],{"class":229}," openai\n",[17,303,304,305,308],{},"Create ",[157,306,307],{},"index.js"," in the project root — that's where we'll write the bot code.",[17,310,311],{},"(Consider adding ESLint to keep your code quality in check.)",[12,313,315],{"id":314},"writing-the-code","Writing the code",[17,317,318],{},"The fun part. I won't comment every line, but I'll keep it simple so you can build your own bot.",[320,321,323],"h3",{"id":322},"discord-bot","Discord bot",[17,325,326],{},"First, the Discord bot code. Discord.js's npm page has an example:",[210,328,332],{"className":329,"code":330,"language":331,"meta":215,"style":215},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","const { Client, GatewayIntentBits } = require('discord.js');\nconst client = new Client({ intents: [GatewayIntentBits.Guilds] });\n\nclient.on('ready', () => {\n  console.log(`Logged in as ${client.user.tag}!`);\n});\n\nclient.on('interactionCreate', async interaction => {\n  if (!interaction.isChatInputCommand()) return;\n\n  if (interaction.commandName === 'ping') {\n    await interaction.reply('Pong!');\n  }\n});\n\nclient.login(TOKEN);\n","js",[157,333,334,372,391,397,420,452,458,463,489,516,521,538,557,563,568,573],{"__ignoreMap":215},[219,335,336,340,344,347,350,353,356,359,363,366,369],{"class":221,"line":222},[219,337,339],{"class":338},"sOudu","const",[219,341,343],{"class":342},"s8XSl"," { ",[219,345,346],{"class":236},"Client",[219,348,349],{"class":342},", ",[219,351,352],{"class":236},"GatewayIntentBits",[219,354,355],{"class":342}," } ",[219,357,358],{"class":338},"=",[219,360,362],{"class":361},"scAaK"," require",[219,364,365],{"class":342},"(",[219,367,368],{"class":229},"'discord.js'",[219,370,371],{"class":342},");\n",[219,373,374,376,379,382,385,388],{"class":221,"line":233},[219,375,339],{"class":338},[219,377,378],{"class":236}," client",[219,380,381],{"class":338}," =",[219,383,384],{"class":338}," new",[219,386,387],{"class":361}," Client",[219,389,390],{"class":342},"({ intents: [GatewayIntentBits.Guilds] });\n",[219,392,393],{"class":221,"line":242},[219,394,396],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":395},true,"\n",[219,398,400,403,406,408,411,414,417],{"class":221,"line":399},4,[219,401,402],{"class":342},"client.",[219,404,405],{"class":361},"on",[219,407,365],{"class":342},[219,409,410],{"class":229},"'ready'",[219,412,413],{"class":342},", () ",[219,415,416],{"class":338},"=>",[219,418,419],{"class":342}," {\n",[219,421,423,426,429,431,434,437,439,442,444,447,450],{"class":221,"line":422},5,[219,424,425],{"class":342},"  console.",[219,427,428],{"class":361},"log",[219,430,365],{"class":342},[219,432,433],{"class":229},"`Logged in as ${",[219,435,436],{"class":342},"client",[219,438,35],{"class":229},[219,440,441],{"class":342},"user",[219,443,35],{"class":229},[219,445,446],{"class":342},"tag",[219,448,449],{"class":229},"}!`",[219,451,371],{"class":342},[219,453,455],{"class":221,"line":454},6,[219,456,457],{"class":342},"});\n",[219,459,461],{"class":221,"line":460},7,[219,462,396],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":395},[219,464,466,468,470,472,475,477,480,484,487],{"class":221,"line":465},8,[219,467,402],{"class":342},[219,469,405],{"class":361},[219,471,365],{"class":342},[219,473,474],{"class":229},"'interactionCreate'",[219,476,349],{"class":342},[219,478,479],{"class":338},"async",[219,481,483],{"class":482},"syBk-"," interaction",[219,485,486],{"class":338}," =>",[219,488,419],{"class":342},[219,490,492,495,498,501,504,507,510,513],{"class":221,"line":491},9,[219,493,494],{"class":338},"  if",[219,496,497],{"class":342}," (",[219,499,500],{"class":338},"!",[219,502,503],{"class":342},"interaction.",[219,505,506],{"class":361},"isChatInputCommand",[219,508,509],{"class":342},"()) ",[219,511,512],{"class":338},"return",[219,514,515],{"class":342},";\n",[219,517,519],{"class":221,"line":518},10,[219,520,396],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":395},[219,522,524,526,529,532,535],{"class":221,"line":523},11,[219,525,494],{"class":338},[219,527,528],{"class":342}," (interaction.commandName ",[219,530,531],{"class":338},"===",[219,533,534],{"class":229}," 'ping'",[219,536,537],{"class":342},") {\n",[219,539,541,544,547,550,552,555],{"class":221,"line":540},12,[219,542,543],{"class":338},"    await",[219,545,546],{"class":342}," interaction.",[219,548,549],{"class":361},"reply",[219,551,365],{"class":342},[219,553,554],{"class":229},"'Pong!'",[219,556,371],{"class":342},[219,558,560],{"class":221,"line":559},13,[219,561,562],{"class":342},"  }\n",[219,564,566],{"class":221,"line":565},14,[219,567,457],{"class":342},[219,569,571],{"class":221,"line":570},15,[219,572,396],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":395},[219,574,576,578,581,583,586],{"class":221,"line":575},16,[219,577,402],{"class":342},[219,579,580],{"class":361},"login",[219,582,365],{"class":342},[219,584,585],{"class":236},"TOKEN",[219,587,371],{"class":342},[17,589,590],{},"What this does:",[47,592,593,598,603,613],{},[50,594,595,597],{},[157,596,346],{},": the Discord Client — what we use to interact with Discord's API",[50,599,600,602],{},[157,601,352],{},": Discord's GatewayIntent — defines what our bot does",[50,604,605,608,609,612],{},[157,606,607],{},"client.on('ready', () => { ... })",": what to do when the bot starts — e.g. print \"",[157,610,611],{},"Logged in as ${client.user.tag}!","\" to tell us the bot is ready",[50,614,615,618],{},[157,616,617],{},"client.login(TOKEN)",": log in with the bot's Token from the Discord Developer Portal",[17,620,621,622,625,626,629,630,633],{},"The important pattern is ",[157,623,624],{},"client.on('Event', () => { ... })",". The ",[157,627,628],{},"Event"," is what we listen to. ",[157,631,632],{},"ready"," listens for bot startup.",[17,635,636],{},"Discord has many events — common ones:",[47,638,639,644,650],{},[50,640,641,643],{},[157,642,632],{},": bot has started",[50,645,646,649],{},[157,647,648],{},"interactionCreate",": user invokes a bot command",[50,651,652,655],{},[157,653,654],{},"messageCreate",": user sends a message",[17,657,658,659,661,662,664,665,668,669,661,672,675,676,678],{},"These are the most common. We only need ",[157,660,632],{}," and ",[157,663,654],{},". We also need to set ",[157,666,667],{},"intents"," — what the bot is allowed to do. We need ",[157,670,671],{},"GuildsMessages",[157,673,674],{},"MessageContent",", so modify the example like this in ",[157,677,307],{},":",[210,680,682],{"className":329,"code":681,"language":331,"meta":215,"style":215},"require('dotenv').config()\n\nconst { Client, GatewayIntentBits } = require('discord.js');\n\nconst client = new Client({ intents: [\n  GatewayIntentBits.Guilds,\n  GatewayIntentBits.GuildMessages,\n  GatewayIntentBits.MessageContent,\n]});\n\nclient.on('ready', () => {\n  console.log(`Logged in as ${client.user.tag}!`);\n});\n\nclient.on('messageCreate', async message => {\n  console.log('User message:', message.content);\n});\n\nclient.login(process.env.DISCORD_TOKEN);\n",[157,683,684,703,707,731,735,750,755,760,765,770,774,790,814,818,822,844,858,863,868],{"__ignoreMap":215},[219,685,686,689,691,694,697,700],{"class":221,"line":222},[219,687,688],{"class":361},"require",[219,690,365],{"class":342},[219,692,693],{"class":229},"'dotenv'",[219,695,696],{"class":342},").",[219,698,699],{"class":361},"config",[219,701,702],{"class":342},"()\n",[219,704,705],{"class":221,"line":233},[219,706,396],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":395},[219,708,709,711,713,715,717,719,721,723,725,727,729],{"class":221,"line":242},[219,710,339],{"class":338},[219,712,343],{"class":342},[219,714,346],{"class":236},[219,716,349],{"class":342},[219,718,352],{"class":236},[219,720,355],{"class":342},[219,722,358],{"class":338},[219,724,362],{"class":361},[219,726,365],{"class":342},[219,728,368],{"class":229},[219,730,371],{"class":342},[219,732,733],{"class":221,"line":399},[219,734,396],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":395},[219,736,737,739,741,743,745,747],{"class":221,"line":422},[219,738,339],{"class":338},[219,740,378],{"class":236},[219,742,381],{"class":338},[219,744,384],{"class":338},[219,746,387],{"class":361},[219,748,749],{"class":34